      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ffc54982ecf.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ffacb44a1a8.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ffb186e40ce.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ffb329c0997.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ffaa532f71c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ffa859a5fd3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ffa5428f545.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ffa39a72779.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ffa3c33fa7e.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ffa3eae9c25.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff59ec88fe5.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff595223429.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff9ac72dadc.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff89b52ecc6.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff927289b83.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff8de2dd346.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff82d1b5706.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff82a6c4e71.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff826f323c4.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff76ac157b3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff76eb85b52.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff771ddcad8.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff6759edc21.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff685dd3898.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ff6887450ec.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/68ffb7f7a4835.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; .JSON Update&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Adjustment&lt;/em&gt;: Just a quick update to all .JSON files within the Graphics Packs. I miss-typed a comma on line 8 on each one, which prevented installing them on BCML properly. I do sincerely apologise for that. And a big shoutout to the person who made me aware of my mistake. Thankyou so much!&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h3&gt;                              SleepyChu-96 proudly presents...&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor SelectedElement"&gt;                   &lt;u&gt;KITSUNE - The Fox Companion MOD!&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Ever wondered what it'd be like if you could traverse the land of Hyrule with a new 'furry' buddy? Well my friends, the wait is over!&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;br&gt;See, our wonderous 'beasty-boy' &lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Wolf Link&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;; unfortunately was summoned back to the Twilight Realm by our sweet, dear Princess Midna. However, in his stead: we can now venture around the plains and fields with the in-game foxes!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h2&gt;WHAT THIS MOD DOES:&lt;/h2&gt;This mod allows you to swap out Wolf Link's model, for the Fox model found in the &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Game Files&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; instead. &lt;b&gt;BUT THAT'S NOT ALL IT DOES! &lt;/b&gt;Wolf Link's SFX has also been completely overhauled and reworked to give a more &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;authentic and immersive experience&lt;/span&gt;. As such, now instead of hearing a wolf's howl, growls, barks and snarls - you will now hear certain sounds that naturally come from a fox!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Each individual &lt;b&gt;BFWAV&lt;/b&gt; audio file that is located within Wolf Link's &lt;b&gt;BARS&lt;/b&gt; archive, has been painstakingly chosen, altered, and adjusted so your ears will hopefully not bleed!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Lastly; now you get to &lt;b&gt;CHOOSE&lt;/b&gt; what kind of fox you'd like to travel with! I've gone ahead and made &lt;b&gt;8&lt;/b&gt; different variants to choose from. &lt;b&gt;2&lt;/b&gt; of these foxes can already be found within the Vanilla Game experience; but the other &lt;b&gt;6&lt;/b&gt; have been created solely for this mod. You will find each of the fox variants below:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt; &lt;b&gt;The Grasslands Fox&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;i&gt;[Can be found within the Vanilla Game experience.]&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Snowcoat Fox &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;[Can be found within the Vanilla Game experience.]&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;The Wastelands Fox&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;[*BRAND NEW TEXTURE*]&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;[This Fox Variant was based off the environmental factors found within the Wasteland and Gerudo Regions of Hyrule.]&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;The Highlands Fox&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;[*BRAND NEW TEXTURE*]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;[This Fox Variant was based off the environmental factors found within the Eldin and Tabantha Regions of Hyrule.]&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;The Wild Plains Fox&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;u&gt;[*BRAND NEW TEXTURE*]&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;[This Fox Variant was based off the environmental factors found within the Akkala Region of Hyrule.]&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;The Wetlands Fox&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;[*BRAND NEW TEXTURE*]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;[This Fox Variant was based off the environmental factors found within the Lanayru and Ridgeland Regions of Hyrule.]&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;The Coastlands Fox&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;u&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;[*BRAND NEW TEXTURE*]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/u&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;[This Fox Variant was based off the environmental factors found within the Necluda Region of Hyrule.]&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;The Woodlands Fox&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;[*BRAND NEW TEXTURE*]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;[This Fox Variant was based off the environmental factors found within the Woodland and Faron Regions of Hyrule.]&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Finally I'd like to add a little note: when I originally posted this mod almost 2 years ago now I think; I originally asked my friend &lt;b&gt;H2714 &lt;/b&gt;if it was alright for me to use their &lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;White Spirit Fox&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; texture from their &lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Wolf Link/Sensor Overhaul + skins&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; mod they brought out. The reason I asked if it was alright with them at the time, was because I was having trouble using their mod. For the life of me, I just could not get it to work no matter what I did. And once I decided to have a go at making my own Wolf Link replacer mod, I asked them if it was alright to use their texture as I really liked the look of it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Now that it's been close to 2 years since I made my &lt;b&gt;KITSUNE - The Fox Companion MOD!&lt;/b&gt;, during this overhaul I've been working on; I decided to make the decision to remove &lt;b&gt;H2714&lt;/b&gt;'s texture. This was because I didn't want to have to rely on someone else's work, for something I wanted to make on my own. I thank them from the bottom of my heart for the use of their texture, but now that I've gotten more experience in working with textures myself; I feel it's only fair that I remove theirs, as the mod had taken a slightly different direction than what it originally was.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If any of you find that you're experiencing some difficulty with the mod, I will do my best to help. Even if you just leave some feedback regarding the SFX; I welcome any and all criticism, as long as it's productive, not just being said for the sake that you hate the mod or whatever some people sometimes find time to complain about.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;[&lt;i&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;I say that with as much kindness as I can muster. If anyone does leave a nasty comment, just for the sake of creating drama or anything - please just know that I will completely ignore you. I won't tolerate any form of bullying, whether it be toward me, or anyone else. Fair warning!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/i&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Anyway, I hope you all enjoy the mod! I look forward to hearing your experiences with your vulpine buddies! Thanks again to everyone who have tried this mod out in the past 2 years. I really appreciate it.</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/the_grasslands_fox_55be9_b1610_fd5a7.zip" type="application/zip"/>
